Files and Directories compression:
==================================

1) file compress with few below commands
	# compress filename
	# gzip filename
	# bzip filename

2) the above command will rename the file to compressed file with added extention

3) if the file need to be uncompressed will need to run below commands
	# uncompress filename.zip
	# gunzip filename.gz
	# bunzip filename.bg

4) Compress the idrectory we use tar
	# tar -cvf tarfile.tar <source directory> ====> Convert a directory into file
	# tar -xvf tarfile.tar		=========> extract the content from tar file
	# tar -tvf tarfile.tar		=========> Show the content of tar file
	# tar -rvf tarfile.tar <new directory/file> ===> This will add new file/directory to existing tar file

5) /var file system cleanup steps:
Step1: first need to validate the alert
	# df -h /var
Step2: identify whic file is occupying in /var
	# du -sh * =====> identify which file is occupying more space
Step3: copy the high sized fileinto other file system
	# cp /var/log/messages /backup/message
	# ls -l /backup/messages
Step4: nullify original active file
	# > messages OR cat /dev/null > messages
Step5: compress backup file and move to source path
	# gzip /backup/messages
	# mv /backup/messages /var/log/messages_15092025.gz

dd if=/dev/zero of=/backup/oracle/file1 bs=100M count=2
dd if=/dev/zero of=/backup/oracle/file2 bs=100M count=2
dd if=/dev/zero of=/backup/oracle/file3 bs=100M count=2

